{"id": 223769574, "title": "Leclerc ends Monaco jinx with dream F1 home victory", "text": "Ferrari\u2019s Charles Leclerc won the Monaco Grand Prix to become the first home winner of Formula One\u2019s showcase race since Louis Chiron raced around the city streets in 1931. Sunday\u2019s thrilling victory was the first time the 26-year-old had stood on the Monaco podium in six attempts, and it came after two standing starts from pole position in a race halted when first-lap collisions took out a fifth of the field. McLaren\u2019s Oscar Piastri finished second, 7.1 seconds behind, with Ferrari\u2019s Carlos Sainz Jr third. Red Bull\u2019s championship leader and 2023 Monaco winner Max Verstappen started and finished sixth, only the third time in eight races this season that the triple world champion has been beaten. Leclerc\u2019s Monaco triumph ends years of frustration at his home race by taking the jewel in the Formula One calendar from pole at his third attempt. A tearful Leclerc said: \u201cNo words can explain this. It means a lot, it\u2019s the race that made me dream of becoming an F1 driver.\u201d", "summary": "Ferrari&#039;s Charles Leclerc, the only F1 driver born and raised in the area, finally wins his home race in Monte Carlo.", "url": "https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2024/5/26/leclerc-ends-monaco-jinx-with-dream-f1-home-victory?traffic_source=rss", "image": "https://www.aljazeera.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/05/2024-05-26T154914Z_2107349606_UP1EK5Q17Y0NM_RTRMADP_3_MOTOR-F1-MONACO-1716738644.jpg?resize=1920%2C1440", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 16:30:04", "author": "Al Jazeera,Apps Support", "authors": ["Al Jazeera", "Apps Support"], "language": "en", "source_country": "qa", "sentiment": -0.116}